headline: US STI testing sales drop amid “multifactorial” causes
summary: GlobalData analysis reveals that in H1 2025, sales volume for chlamydia/gonorrhoea tests across US healthcare sites and other facilities decreased by 1.7% versus H1 2024, and by 27.8% for tests targeting bacterial vaginosis.
